<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: TEEN CHARGED WITH MURDER IN RAMPAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A teen-age gang member who allegedly killed a student and critically wounded a 
man picking up his daughter during a shooting rampage near a South-Central Los 
Angeles junior high school has been charged with murder. 
</P>
<P>
Eliazar Bivian, 15, was shot twice in the head Friday and died outside George 
Washington Carver Junior High School last week. 
</P>
<P>
The 14-year-old suspect, whose name was not released because of his age, also 
allegedly shot and critically wounded Jose Luis Mendez, 41, who was meeting his 
daughter near a sports field at the rear of the school. The suspect was 
expected to be arraigned today. 
</P>
<P>
The teen-ager, who also allegedly fired off a round at two 13-year-old boys but 
missed, was charged at Eastlake Juvenile Court with one count of murder and 
three counts of attempted murder, Deputy Dist. Atty. Barry Bradley said. 
</P>
<P>
He was also charged with one count of shooting into an inhabited dwelling, for 
firing a shot that barely missed a mother and her infant child at the start of 
his rampage, and felony cruelty to an animal, Bradley said. 
</P>
<P>
The youth also had shot and killed a chicken in an alley near 45th Street and 
Wadsworth Avenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
